The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of scaling techniques and black-box applications of standard algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses online and streaming models, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of discrete optimization and matroid constraints suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
